{"id":"mobilemusic-dkx","title":"Auto-resume playback after Siri voice dictation ends","description":"When the user invokes Siri for voice commands (e.g., taking notes via dictation), audio playback is interrupted but does not automatically resume once Siri/dictation finishes. The app should detect when the audio session interruption ends and resume playback automatically.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-24T12:56:38.667364-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc","updated_at":"2026-02-24T13:11:12.318605-06:00","closed_at":"2026-02-24T13:11:12.318605-06:00","close_reason":"Closed","labels":["audio","enhancement","siri"]}
{"id":"mobilemusic-duc","title":"CarPlay session causes all groups to expand on iPhone","description":"When the CarPlay interface is active and the user then opens the app on their iPhone, all channel groups are expanded. This likely happens because CarPlay navigation triggers state changes that propagate to the iPhone UI. Investigate why CarPlay interaction expands groups and prevent CarPlay state from affecting the iPhone group collapse/expand state.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-02-24T12:56:28.249609-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc","updated_at":"2026-02-24T13:00:31.63942-06:00","closed_at":"2026-02-24T13:00:31.63942-06:00","close_reason":"Closed","labels":["bug","carplay"]}
