{"id":"mobilemusic-jo2","title":"Phase 10: Adaptive Layouts \u0026 Responsive Dimensions","description":"Replace hardcoded sizes with adaptive values. Create dimension utilities, make NowPlayingView/MiniPlayerView/ChannelRowView/EPGView adaptive, and constrain form widths on iPad.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:33:08.443812-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc","updated_at":"2026-02-25T10:33:08.443812-06:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"mobilemusic-jo2","depends_on_id":"mobilemusic-6aa","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:34:05.189522-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc"}]}
{"id":"mobilemusic-jo2.1","title":"Create adaptive dimension utilities","description":"Build AdaptiveLayout.swift with size-class-aware constants: channel icons (40-\u003e56pt), artwork (200-\u003e300+pt), buttons, spacing. Use @ScaledMetric where appropriate for Dynamic Type support. Provide a clean API like AdaptiveLayout.channelIconSize that returns the right value based on horizontal size class.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:35:44.20411-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc","updated_at":"2026-02-25T10:35:44.20411-06:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"mobilemusic-jo2.1","depends_on_id":"mobilemusic-jo2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:35:44.204779-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc"}]}
{"id":"mobilemusic-jo2.2","title":"Make NowPlayingView adaptive","description":"Horizontal layout on iPad landscape (artwork left, controls right). Scale artwork to 300-400pt on iPad. Increase control spacing and button sizes. Use horizontalSizeClass to switch between compact (vertical stack) and regular (horizontal split) layouts.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:35:49.37501-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc","updated_at":"2026-02-25T10:35:49.37501-06:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"mobilemusic-jo2.2","depends_on_id":"mobilemusic-jo2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:35:49.375678-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc"}]}
{"id":"mobilemusic-jo2.3","title":"Make MiniPlayerView adaptive","description":"Larger channel logo on iPad, show more detail (group name, EPG program info) in regular width. Remove hardcoded 49px tab bar padding and calculate dynamically. Ensure mini player looks good at all iPad widths including Split View.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:35:54.546483-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc","updated_at":"2026-02-25T10:35:54.546483-06:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"mobilemusic-jo2.3","depends_on_id":"mobilemusic-jo2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:35:54.547156-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc"}]}
{"id":"mobilemusic-jo2.4","title":"Make ChannelRowView and channel lists adaptive","description":"Larger icons on iPad (use AdaptiveLayout dimensions), show more detail per row. Consider LazyVGrid layout on iPad landscape for a grid of channels instead of a single-column list.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:35:59.715348-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc","updated_at":"2026-02-25T10:35:59.715348-06:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"mobilemusic-jo2.4","depends_on_id":"mobilemusic-jo2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:35:59.716051-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc"}]}
{"id":"mobilemusic-jo2.5","title":"Make EPGView adaptive for wider screens","description":"Use extra iPad width for a timeline/grid view showing multiple hours of EPG data side by side. On compact width, keep the existing vertical list. Consider a horizontal scroll timeline similar to traditional TV guide apps.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:36:04.886214-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc","updated_at":"2026-02-25T10:36:04.886214-06:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"mobilemusic-jo2.5","depends_on_id":"mobilemusic-jo2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:36:04.886891-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc"}]}
{"id":"mobilemusic-jo2.6","title":"Constrain form widths on iPad","description":"Cap SettingsView and AddProviderView form widths at ~600pt so they don't stretch full-width on iPad. Use .frame(maxWidth:) or .containerRelativeFrame() to center forms on wider screens.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:36:10.071842-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc","updated_at":"2026-02-25T10:36:10.071842-06:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"mobilemusic-jo2.6","depends_on_id":"mobilemusic-jo2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-25T10:36:10.072423-06:00","created_by":"lecaptainc"}]}
